    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES
        (FIGURE 34)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302134">FIGURE 34</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302134" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302134" filename="../figg13/g1302134.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 34. Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Partially drive the output shaft forward to provide clearance for the auxiliary countershaft
                removal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302135">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302135" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302135" filename="../figg13/g1302135.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Drive Output Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the upper countershaft shim gauge from the rear of the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302136">left, Figure 36</hotlnk>). Remove the countershaft rear bearing race from the
                auxiliary housing bore (right). Repeat this procedure for the lower countershaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302136" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302136" filename="../figg13/g1302136.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Countershaft Shim &#38; Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When the shim gauge is removed, the countershaft will fall loose in the auxiliary section.
                        Provide support for the countershaft.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To replace the countershaft bearings, use a jaw puller and bearing separator to remove the
                bearings from each end of the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302137">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302137" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302137" filename="../figg13/g1302137.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
